      "message": "\u003e This should suffice at the API level. If necessary, impl can route the request to \".../detail\" depending on QueryOptions specified.\n\nTrue. Actually, technically, you can use GetChange API with options defined here [1] to achieve the same result as GetChangeDetail. So I\u0027m thinking we just drop the support for calling `detail` flavor API. WDYT?\n\n\n\u003e Also, please test end-to-end that this actually works as intended.\n\u003e Maybe we should have a simple demo/ subpackage with bare bones main.go where one can easily change input+ RPC and then log output of a command?\n\nWill do :) \n\n\n[1]: https://gerrit-review.googlesource.com/Documentation/rest-api-changes.html#labels",
